<item>
            <title>[MNG-3545] Option -P-profile overridden if profile is activebyDefault</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-3545</link>
                <project id="12316922" key="MNG">Maven (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In maven 2.0.9, deactivating a profile &quot;foo&quot; that is declared and marked activeByDefault in the local POM does not work, as in DefaultProfileManager.java:227 all activeByDefault profiles are added if no profile is explicitly given (&quot;-Pbar&quot;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the attached zip, run &lt;br/&gt;
 mvn -P-foo help:active-profiles&lt;br/&gt;
and note that foo &lt;b&gt;is&lt;/b&gt; active.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch fixes these issues by checking all default-activated profiles against the exclusions list when they are added &quot;by default&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
