                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14413105" author="elca-dbd" created="Thu, 24 Apr 2008 04:02:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;While making the patch for trunk : Is it intentional that the roles of + and - are swapped, i.e. &lt;b&gt;+foo&lt;/b&gt; &lt;em&gt;deactivates&lt;/em&gt; foo yet -foo &lt;b&gt;activates&lt;/b&gt; it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14413065" author="elca-dbd" created="Thu, 24 Apr 2008 04:03:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch file. The technique works for 2.0.9 too; in 2.1 use &quot;-P+foo&quot; to turn &lt;em&gt;off&lt;/em&gt; foo with this patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14413124" author="ID134349" created="Thu, 1 May 2008 12:33:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I hope + (or nothing at all) means activate, and - means deactivate. It&apos;s just natural to understand the minus sign as subtraction, in which you are taking away something that already exists.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14413014" author="pgier" created="Thu, 1 May 2008 13:05:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes,&lt;tt&gt;+&lt;/tt&gt; or nothing for activate and &lt;tt&gt;-&lt;/tt&gt; for deactivate, that is my understanding.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ll test 2.1 also to make sure that the behaviour is the same.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14413053" author="pgier" created="Thu, 15 May 2008 16:23:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added an integration test for this and it seems to be working correctly now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14413712" author="jdcasey" created="Wed, 3 Sep 2008 16:59:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Adding fix-for for both 2.0.10 and 2.1.0-M1, since 2.1.0-M1 will actually be released first and may not incorporate all of the eventual issue fixes released in 2.0.10.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17998457" author="JIRAUSER302100" created="Sat, 5 Jul 2025 16:37:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven/issues/5404&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven#5404&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
